				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\mathrm{g}}_{\mathrm{cat}.}^{-1}$$\end{document}  h−1 (Fig. 11g) was reached at 70 mA cm−2 in a three-phase flow cell exhibiting stable operation over a period of 8 h (Fig. 11h). Thus, compared to conventional Ni–N4 coordination, the electrocatalytic H2O2-producing properties of Ni SACs via the 2e− ORR were improved by building the Ni–N2O2 coordination configuration.Fig. 11
